Text.Value: I don't know. It was such a huge mistake. I'm so sorry.
I think so. You should probably go.
Ugh. I wish I could say I don't understand. But I know what those tricky fuckers are like.
You should go.
You sure, soldier?

EditorData.NodeContext: A little soft; a little wounded; she's asking if the player really wants her to leave camp permanently.

Text.Value: But I know better than anyone how tricky those devilish fuckers are. They'll make you think you're a god, 'til you wake up and find yourself face down in the mud.
Maybe you can stay on the team, but we ought to take some space personally.
They'll promise you the world - make you believe it, too. Then right when you're relaxed, yoink! There goes the rug, right out from under you.
You and I both know how tricky these devilish fuckers can be.

EditorData.NodeContext: the tears are drying up now. She and the player are on the path to reconciliation.

Text.Value: My curiosity got the better of me.
What?

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: Karlach is very hurt by the player choosing to sleep with Mizora, who she hates and who works for her old mistress Zariel
EditorData.NodeContext: acknowledges  the player after having been crying. She's really let down by the player so her hurt is shining through.

Text.Value: I don't want to tell you what to do, or who to do it with. But I won't stand around and watch Mizora do with you as she pleases. Anyone but her.

EditorData.NodeContext: She and the player are on the path to reconciliation.

Text.Value: I'm protective of my freedom. But I understand your point, too.
Motherfucker! You scared me.

EditorData.NodeContext: Good natured/ relief. She thought the player was dumping her.

Text.Value: You'll have to get let that go.
Friends, then. That'll do. Well. I should go get busy with... being your friend. Bye.

EditorData.NodeContext: A little weakly. This is a breakup. She's sad.

Text.Value: This isn't about me, Wyll. It's about you.

EditorData.NodeContext: Angry, but on the path to reconciliation

Text.Value: When they've got you wrapped around their finger, everything seems like such a good idea. Then you blink, and you realise... shit.

EditorData.NodeContext: She and the player are on the path to reconciliation.

Text.Value: We don't need them. We have each other. Ourselves. Life. What else could we want?
Personally, maybe. But I still want you to stay on the team.
My relationship with Mizora is complicated. And it's between the two of us.
Not exactly. I care about you, but I want my freedom, too.
Look. I don't own you. I can't tell you what to do - and I wouldn't. But Mizora?
You have it. I don't mind who you spend your time with - but agents of Zariel are a different category.
Let's just forget all this happened, all right? Gods! I need a drink. Badly.
I'm not mad. I'm... fucking devastated.
I trust you won't make the same mistake twice. Mizora works for Zariel - pure evil.
So. Is that it between us?
Please don't tell me you're still mad that I had a bit of fun with Mizora.
Karlach, I'm sorry for what happened with Mizora. I didn't think it would affect you so much.
If I'd known it would affect you so badly, I wouldn't have.
As a matter of fact, it is.
I'm sorry, Karlach. I wasn't thinking. It was selfish.
No - we belong together.
Feels so strange coming out of my mouth. Erm. Bye, then.

EditorData.NodeContext: False levity. She's leaving the party after the player tells her to go. Heartbroken.

Text.Value: I still care about you. I want to stay. Here - with you. But you were so... so hard before. About Mizora.
I reacted badly. I'm sorry.
But I do have some limits. And anything in Zariel's orbit is just - no. Not ever. If I can hold you to that, we'll be all right.
After everything she's done to Wyll. After everything she would do to me if given the chance. How could you do it?
That's up to you.
Listen, I'm protective of your freedom, too. We're nothing without that. And I don't want to limit you. I just want to... to love you.
After everything she's done to you, Wyll. How could you do it?
I... think I can manage that. Just about. Will have to dig out my big girl boots, but they've got to be around here somewhere.
Wait. I'm sorry. I'm being an arse. Please forgive me.
I care about you. So, so much. I never thought you'd - you'd disrespect both of us like this.
Been there myself. What can you do except try again.
What's the matter?
It really was. I don't know what was going through your head.
You deserve better. You deserve me.

EditorData.NodeContext: She and the player are on the path to reconciliation.

Text.Value: And I want to try again with you. Always.
All right. Hope you burn your tongue on that devil bitch's arse. And don't come crying to me when you realise what a prick you've been.

EditorData.NodeContext: the harshest she will be in the entire game to the player

Text.Value: Is that really how you feel?
Right. Then I guess... I guess this is good-bye?
Yes. We're better off going our separate ways.
I agree. We should take some space in our relationship. But I hope you'll stay on the team.
Yeah. I don't think so. And if you can't understand why that bothers me so much, I think this is it for us.
It's your business. But she's going to hurt you - even worse than she already has. And I don't know if I'm going to stick around to watch it happen.
I care about you. I don't want you to get hurt. And I don't want to invite the Hells into our home. Not again.
It's not really any of your business who I spend my time with.
Let it go? That you slept with an agent of the archdevil who ruined my life, right under my nose?

Synopsis: Player slept with Mizora and discusses it with Karlach.
